The paper deals with the generation of 3D meshes, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The use of Transformer-based architecture and probabilistic modeling suggests that the paper is likely to be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the model to computer graphics and games development suggests that it may also be related to graphics (cs.GR). The use of object classes, voxels, and images as inputs suggests that the paper may also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
